How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Learn more how customers reviews work on Amazon

Customers say

Customers find these lemons flavorful with a sour taste, and appreciate their amazing quality, freshness, and brilliant yellow color. They are big in size and perfect for cooking and drinking, with one customer noting they're great for making lemonade. While many customers consider them expensive, some find them reasonably priced. Customers report issues with rottenness, with several mentioning they arrive rotten every time.

5 out of 5 stars
Conventional Lemon, Unconventionally Good
Ah, the conventional lemon, bright and bold, Picked from a mysterious grove, or so Im told. Was it grown on a farm by a sun-soaked stream? Or maybe on the edge of a freeways dream? No fancy label, no organic boast, Just a lemon doing its citrus most. Slice it open, the juice flows free, Tangy, zesty, pure jubilee. Perfect for tea, fish, or pie, Makes everything sing, gives dishes a try. Its not farm-to-table or artisanal fare, More like, I was grown somewhere. Dont ask where. Sure, it might not come with a story to tell, But itll pucker your mouth just as well. 5/5 for zest, juice, and shine, This humble lemon suits me just fine.

    Reviewed in the United States on June 4, 2023
    Verified Purchase
    With a sharp and intense lemon flavor, these yellow orbs of zest embody the essence of tanginess. Each squeeze released a burst of citrusy goodness that elevated dishes and beverages to unparalleled heights of taste. When life handed me lemons, I didn't simply make lemonade; I concocted a symphony of flavors that danced upon my palate and left me craving more.

    One cannot underestimate the power of fresh-squeezed lemonade, where the essence of these lemons intertwines with sugar and water to create a refreshing elixir that quenches the thirst and invigorates the spirit. The intense lemon flavor cut through the sweetness, offering a perfect balance that was both revitalizing and satisfying. It's a drink that transported you to sun-drenched beaches and moments of pure bliss.

    But the journey doesn't end with lemonade alone. Oh no! For me, these lemons are a versatile ally in the realm of culinary delights. I used as a marinade for shrimp tacos. They infused a burst of tangy zest that brought the seafood to life, turning an ordinary dish into a flavor-packed fiesta for the taste buds. The high intensity of flavor in these lemons adds a zing that cuts through the richness of the shrimp, creating a harmonious balance that is truly irresistible.

    The vibrant yellow skin of lemons is a testament to their invigorating nature, hinting at the treasure that lies within. Their citrusy essence has the power to transform even the simplest of dishes into culinary masterpieces. From roasted chicken to salad dressings and beyond, the possibilities are endless when lemons grace the kitchen.
